Package ide.backend.exceptions

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BreakException
    Thrown if a breakpoint occurs
    CompileException
    Thrown if the compiler cant compile a given program
    FileException
    Thrown if a file can not be loaded into Java
    FunctionNotFoundException
    Thrown if a function can not be found on runtime
    LoadException
    Throw if a file cannot be loaded.
    LockedException
    Exception thrown if attempting to lock a variable that is already locked.
    ProcesFinshedException
    throw if a process has finished executed.
    TypeException
    This exception is thrown when using an operation on the wrong type of variable.
    VariableNotFoundException
    Execption being throw if variable is not found on current stack or current private variables
